      1          /**
      2           * @file
      3           * @defgroup    CLASS_B
      4           * @brief       API020 Safety is used to transfer Class B data over a Class A communication bus.
      5           *
      6           * @details     The strategy of this module is to define receive (RX) and transmit (TX) Class B
      7           *              data channels through the configuration files.
      8           *
      9           *              Receive (RX) Channels:
     10           *
     11           *                  The SRAPI020Safety module keeps track of the received messages on the
     12           *                  communications bus and ensures that the received data is valid. A Class B
     13           *                  module can call SRAPI020Safety__GetRxValue() at any time to check if there is
     14           *                  any valid data from the remote node.
     15           *
     16           *                  The SRAPI020Safety module considers the RX channel valid when the following
     17           *                  conditions are met:
     18           *                      - The last message was received within the timeout period.
     19           *                      - The time between the last two received messages was less than the
     20           *                          timeout period.
     21           *                      - The last two received messages were sequential messages.
     22           *
     23           *              Transmit (TX) Channels:
     24           *
     25           *                  The SRAPI020Safety module manages the sequence and timing for transmitted
     26           *                  messages. A Class B module must call SRAPI020Safety__SetTxValue() periodically
     27           *                  in order to maintain a valid sequence of messages. The time between calls must
     28           *                  be less than the timeout specified in the configuration.
     29           *
     30           *                  The SRAPI020Safety module sends the messages with valid sequence numbers as
     31           *                  long as the SRAPI020Safety__SetTxValue() function is called with the
     32           *                  appropriate timing.
     33           *
     34           *              The receiver will not consider the value valid until two sequential message have
     35           *              been received. The sender can send two sequential messages in rapid succession to
     36           *              force this condition.
     37           *
     38           * @copyright   Copyright 2017 Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     39           */
     40          
